The collection\+View\+Scroll\+Bars style will be used as the default style for Items\+View\+Renderer (the base renderer for Collection\+View and Carousel\+View. We have to use a style to set up the scrollbars because there is currently no way to add them via code. When the renderer is created, we wrap its Context\textquotesingle{}s theme with collection\+View\+Theme; that way, the collection\+View\+Scroll\+Bars style will be defined. With the style defined (and with the collection\+View\+Style attribute defined in attrs.\+xml), we can apply the collection\+View\+Scroll\+Bars style explicitly to the renderer we are creating (and avoid forcing every child control to have scrollbars). \Hypertarget{a02587_a2552edbb3930cf55e52faa61f60ac6d6_a2552edbb3930cf55e52faa61f60ac6d6}\index{com.companyname.weighttrackapp.R.style@{com.companyname.weighttrackapp.R.style}!scrollViewTheme@{scrollViewTheme}}
